Business Summary




Trinidad and Tobago NGL Limited is an investment holding company. The Company is formed to hold Phoenix Park Gas Processors Limited's (PPGPL or Phoenix Park) Class B Shares. Phoenix Park’s business consists of natural gas processing, natural gas liquids (NGLs) aggregation, fractionation and marketing. PPGPL is a producer and marketer of propane, mixed butane, isobutane and natural gasoline in Trinidad and Tobago. Phoenix Park owns and operates a gas processing straddle plant based approximately three cryogenic trains with a design capacity totaling over 1.95 billion cubic feet per day (bcfd); over three NGLs fractionators that separate propane, butane and natural gasoline; a butane splitting facility that produces normal butane and isobutene; over six product storage tanks, and a marine loading dock. PPGPL leases and operates an additional marine loading dock facility from Yara Trinidad Limited. The Company is a subsidiary of The National Gas Company of Trinidad and Tobago Limited.(Source: Company's Website)


